Package: cdemu-client
Architecture: all
Depends: python, python-dbus, cdemu-daemon (>= 1.3.0), ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Provides: ${python:Provides}
Description: A simple command-line client to control CDEmu daemon
 This is cdemu-client, a simple command-line client for controlling the
 CDEmu daemon. It is part of the CDEmu suite, a free, GPL CD/DVD-ROM device 
 emulator for Linux.
 .
 It provides a way to perform the key tasks related to controlling the CDEmu
 daemon, such as loading and unloading devices, displaying devices' status and
 retrieving/setting devices' debug masks.

